    Third day descending from Elder Heartwood through hills back toward Territory Two boundary. Easier descent, retracing path. Oakshade and Mossmantle share Elder Heartwood stories - Territory Seven mineral depletion solved with complete ecosystem framework, boundary dispute resolved by reframing collaboration. Plants absolutely confident Elder Heartwood sees patterns and connections they cannot. Kira recognizes she's changed during journey - more confident, trusts rhythm, reads terrain better. Scout has grown too in partnership. Reflecting that journey taught real skills (walking, adaptation, trust) but still waiting for THE answer about human survival needs. Those skills matter but don't solve fundamental problem. Elder Heartwood will bridge the incompatible frameworks. Realizing the answer will help beyond just her - creates understanding for whole network. Evening camp, same spot as before. Tomorrow reaching Territory Two boundary to begin journey home. Six more days walking familiar territories. Then waiting for Elder Heartwood's wisdom - weeks or months. Falling asleep with hope that the answer will be enough. Still counting on external authority to solve what journey couldn't.
  </summary>
